headlines.description: — Deshaun Watson had a pair of go-ahead touchdown passes in the first half and threw for two more scores in the fourth quarter to help the Houston Texans pull away and beat the Detroit Lions 41-25...
headlines.shortLinkText: Deshaun Watson's 4 TDs lift Texans to 41-25 win over Lions

headlines.description: — Antonio Gibson ran for three touchdowns, Alex Smith had a scoring pass and Washington at least temporarily moved into first place in the woeful NFC East with a 41-16 Thanksgiving victory over the Dallas Cowboys on Thursday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gibson, Washington roll past Cowboys 41-16 on Thanksgiving

events.name: Las Vegas Raiders at Atlanta Falcons

headlines.description: — Deion Jones returned an interception 67 yards for a touchdown, Matt Ryan threw a pair of short scoring passes, and the Atlanta Falcons thoroughly dominated Derek Carr and the bumbling Las Vegas Raiders 43-6 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones returns pick for TD, Falcons rout Carr, Raiders 43-6

events.name: Los Angeles Chargers at Buffalo Bills

headlines.description: — Tre’Davious White’s fourth-quarter interception set up Tyler Bass’ 43-yard field goal, helping the Buffalo Bills hold off the Los Angeles Chargers for a 27-17 win Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bills hang on in sloppy 27-17 win over Chargers

events.name: New York Giants at Cincinnati Bengals

headlines.description: — The New York Giants lost starting quarterback Daniel Jones to a hamstring injury in the second half on Sunday, but they generated enough offense to beat the Cincinnati Bengals 19-17.
headlines.shortLinkText: QB Jones injured in Giants' win over Burrow-less Bengals

headlines.description: — Derrick Henry carried the Tennessee Titans into the AFC South lead Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Henry leads Titans' run to AFC South lead 45-26  over Colts

headlines.description: — Chad Beebe caught a 10-yard touchdown pass with 46 seconds left for Minnesota shortly after he muffed a punt that let Carolina pad its lead. Then Joey Slye missed a 54-yard field goal try with 1 second remaining that preserved a 28-27 victory by the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Beebe amends for fumble with TD as Vikes top Panthers 28-27

events.name: Arizona Cardinals at New England Patriots

headlines.description: — Nick Folk kicked a 50-yard field goal as time expired, and the New England Patriots rallied in the second half to beat the Arizona Cardinals 20-17 Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pats keep playoff hopes alive with 20-17 win over Cardinals

events.name: Miami Dolphins at New York Jets

headlines.description: — Ryan Fitzpatrick threw two touchdown passes while starting in place of the injured Tua Tagovailoa and the Miami Dolphins kept the New York Jets winless with a 20-3 victory Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fitzpatrick, Dolphins keep Jets winless with 20-3 victory

headlines.description: — Baker Mayfield took advantage of his best game-day weather in a month, throwing two touchdown passes in Cleveland’s 27-25 victory against Jacksonville on Sunday that kept the Browns squarely in the AFC playoff picture.
headlines.shortLinkText: Browns survive late scare, hold on to beat Jaguars 27-25

events.name: New Orleans Saints at Denver Broncos

headlines.description: — Taysom Hill's two touchdown runs led the New Orleans Saints to a 31-3 win Sunday over the Denver Broncos, who were thrust into a <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Hill leads Saints to 31-3 rout of QB-challenged Broncos

events.name: San Francisco 49ers at Los Angeles Rams

headlines.description: — Robbie Gould made a 42-yard field goal as time expired, and the San Francisco 49ers snapped their three-game losing streak with a 23-20 victory over the Los Angeles Rams on Sunday, sweeping their season series for the second straight year.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gould hits FG at gun, 49ers hand Rams first SoFi loss, 23-20

events.name: Kansas City Chiefs at Tampa Bay Buccaneers

headlines.description: — Patrick Mahomes threw for 462 yards and three touchdowns to outplay Tom Brady and lead the Kansas City Chiefs to a 27-24 victory over the Tampa Bay Buccaneers on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes, Hill have huge day, Chiefs hold off Bucs 27-24

events.name: Chicago Bears at Green Bay Packers

headlines.description: — Aaron Rodgers threw four touchdown passes and the Green Bay Packers beat the slumping Chicago Bears 41-25 on Sunday night to pad their NFC North lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rodgers' 4 TD passes help Packers roll over Bears 41-25

headlines.description: — DK Metcalf again made the Philadelphia Eagles regret passing him up in the draft.
headlines.shortLinkText: Metcalf, Wilson lead Seahawks over Eagles 23-17

headlines.description: — The Pittsburgh Steelers are still perfect, even amid all their imperfections.
headlines.shortLinkText: Steelers overcome rust, short-handed Ravens to move to 11-0
